In your message you write:
&gt; 
&gt; I've seen several pieces of mail time out after three days
&gt; &gt;from here at Michigan destined for sites in Norway because
&gt; of host name lookup failures.  Our connections to the internet
&gt; as a whole are as good as anyone could ask for.  anyone else
&gt; having these problems?
&gt; 
&gt; In particular, I can't resolve tor.nta.no.

I received the following message from Norway, a while back.  I believe 
that it explains the current problem.

Tim Kehres

Forwarded Message:


SUBJECT : temporary address change
SENT BY : Harald Eikrem &lt;postmaster%vax.runit.unit.uninett@TOR.nta.no&gt;
SENT TO : &lt;cmu-tek-tcp-request@cc.cmu.edu&gt;,
